Reasoning: 
1. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper focuses on improving the optimization of recurrent neural networks, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses various optimization algorithms for deep neural networks, which is a core topic in machine learning.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper deals with improving the performance of recurrent neural networks, which is a subfield of AI.
4. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper includes experiments on document classification using graph neural networks, which is a common application in computer vision.
5. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper includes experiments on hyperparameter optimization for fully connected networks, which is a common task in natural language processing.
